According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global Disposable Compostable Tableware Market was valued at USD 6.50 billion in 2025 and is projected to grow from USD 6.77 billion in 2026 to USD 8.62 billion by 2034, registering a CAGR of 4.2% during the forecast period. The market is witnessing steady growth as governments worldwide implement stringent regulations on single-use plastics while businesses and consumers increasingly embrace sustainable alternatives. Rising demand from the foodservice industry, continuous innovation in biodegradable materials, and expanding corporate sustainability initiatives are expected to support long-term market expansion.
Disposable compostable tableware has emerged as a practical solution for reducing plastic waste by utilizing renewable raw materials such as sugarcane bagasse, bamboo fiber, corn starch, and polylactic acid (PLA). These products offer environmentally responsible alternatives for restaurants, catering services, events, and takeaway food businesses while supporting circular economy objectives. Ongoing improvements in product strength, heat resistance, and moisture protection are further expanding their commercial applications across hospitality and food packaging sectors.
